10
00:00:54,437 --> 00:00:58,054
Several legends all explain how Go originated.

11
00:00:58,057 --> 00:01:01,694
In the book of Natural History (Bowuzhi in Chinese),

12
00:01:01,697 --> 00:01:04,974
it says the Emperor of Shun invented Go to teach his son wisdom.

13
00:01:04,977 --> 00:01:07,444
In Postscript of Hearsay History (Lushihouji in Chinese),

14
00:01:07,447 --> 00:01:10,471
the hero became the Emperor of Yao,

15
00:01:10,474 --> 00:01:14,364
who made Go as a tool
to teach his son how to be pure and virtuous.

16
00:01:14,367 --> 00:01:17,454
An ancient tomb of the Liao Dynasty in Inner Mongolia

17
00:01:17,457 --> 00:01:20,694
has unearthed the endgame of Go in a game:

18
00:01:20,697 --> 00:01:23,034
the Go board has a 13¡Á13 grid of lines,

19
00:01:23,037 --> 00:01:28,064
